Change has been successfully merged
I started a small discussion about the `xyz.openbmc_project.LeakDetect` namespace on the design doc. I prefer we choose something different.
Done, changed to xyz.openbmc_project.Cooling

really?    Leak detectors were added in 2023.1 release. They have a custom state schema per webinar below.   They didn't provide a message to say they had detected a leak?

the webinar says they can describe leak detectors and their state at 15:42 https://youtu.be/UKaLVR3HGSY?feature=shared

did you ask the redfish forum for advice?
Done
hmmm was commenting on https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/73707?forceReload=true

Just "containing".  "detectors" is a type.  We preclude using the the type.

https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/blob/master/requirements.md#directed-associations-should-not-codify-type

I think I'd prefer we use monitored_by / monitoring or measured_by / measuring.

Sure, dropped the new association and uses the existing monitored_by association in Item interface. Updated description and added detector to "required_endpoint_interfaces" for existing monitored_by association.
I'd rather not create new top-level parts of the hierarchy ("LeakDetection" in this case).  Can we put this under State, Sensor, Metric, or Condition?
State seems to be closest match so move it under State/Leak.
Should we use an enum for this?  Do you have error conditions where this needs to be Unknown?
The state can either be enabled or disabled hence boolean.. Can you provide an example of an error state?
As we discussed changed this to an enum.

If these come from a Redfish schema, can we reference that schema here?

If you're only planning to implement LeakSensingRope, should we limit it just that one?

> If these come from a Redfish schema, can we reference that schema here?
> 
Sure, will add the Redfish Schema reference.
LeakSensingRope is not in Redfish Schema yet. I have requested Redfish Forum to add Rope type to Detector types https://redfishforum.com/thread/1089/extend-leakdetectortype-leak-detection-cable and they are willing for it.

> If you're only planning to implement LeakSensingRope, should we limit it just that one?

My implementation is parsing all types coming from EM, so its a generic logic https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/75329/4/src/LeakDetection/LeakDetector.hpp#45. Let me know if you think otherwise?
As we discussed changed the wording to LeakSensingCable and removed the FloatSwitch and MositureSensor from enum as they haven't been implemented yet.
Already made a comment elsewhere on this one.
Done
Not entirely please with this being a new top-level part of the hierarchy.  See discussion on file name.
Done
What kind of "aggregation"?  I think what you're saying is that this just reflects the worst case "leak detected" state, but let's make it clear.

Refer to LeakDetectorGroups Status 
 property in https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/LeakDetection.v1_1_0.json. 
 
 "longDescription": "This object shall contain a group of leak detection equipment that reports a unified status."
 
 Also, i have moved DetectorGroup to a different patch, so you can review it there https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/75701. Marking this comment resolved here.
Addressed & replied to your comments. Thanks
DetectorState?

Sorry, In my previous commit, I missed using the DetectorState enum in this definition. I have now updated it to use the correct type, which is DetectorState. I did not define the property name as DetectorState because it is already defined in Detector.interface.yaml and I thought it would be redundant to reuse the prefix "Detector". Please let me know if you have any concerns with this reasoning.
Done
